8.42	The_Honeymoon_Killers	The Honeymoon Killers	The Honeymoon Killers is a 1970 American film written and directed by Leonard Kastle, and starring Shirley Stoler and Tony Lo Bianco. It tells the story of Martha Beck and Raymond Fernandez, the notorious "lonely hearts killers" who murdered at least 12 women in the 1940s. The soundtrack is from the first movement of the 6th Symphony of Gustav Mahler.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b2/The_honeymoon_killers_poster.jpg/220px-The_honeymoon_killers_poster.jpg
